Announcing JavaLog-1.0 Beta4 

We are pleased to announce the release of version 1.0 Beta 4 of JavaLog.

JavaLog is a Prolog interpreter written in Java(tm) designed to allow easy
integration between Java and Prolog. JavaLog was developed by The Objects and
Visualization Group (http://www.exa.unicen.edu.ar/~mcampo/gov/) and is currently
used in several research projects related to artificial intelligence supported 
by Object Oriented concepts for Software Development. 

JavaLog has the following features:

   -It enables the creation and usage of Java objects in Prolog programs, mixing
    Logic/OO paradigms. 
   -It preprocess Java methods with embedded Prolog.
   -It supports the manage of common knowledge of several instances of our
    Prolog interpreter by means of a blackboard architecture. 
   -It allow the physical distribution of Prolog interpreters using Java RMI and
    logic module mobility. 

For more information about JavaLog, see the JavaLog WWW page at
http://www.exa.unicen.edu.ar/~azunino/
